parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper system can cause poor visibility while driving, especially in inclement weather conditions, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop working suddenly
wipers work intermittently
wipers come on and off on their own
wipers fail to turn off
wipers do not respond to switch input
poor visibility due to wiper failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to slip out of gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
the vehicle coasts to the side of the road
the transmission becomes stuck in a specific gear
and the vehicle is unable to shift into higher gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, and potentially fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal gives way
a popping noise is heard when depressing the brake pedal
the anti-skid system engages
causing the vehicle to pull to one side
and the brakes may not function at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, and potentially fatalities.
symptoms: The dash brake light is constantly on or flashing
the radio has been replaced multiple times
and the glow plug controller does not activate the glow plugs after a hot engine sits for about 15 minutes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not function properly, leading to injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The driver's seat belt will not retract and is very loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the paint and rust protection can cause the vehicle's body to rust, leading to structural integrity issues and potentially safety hazards.
symptoms: The paint starts chipping within 6 months and less than 2500 miles
the roof is now rusted through
and the headliner is hanging down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper system can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents, injuries, and potentially fatalities.
symptoms: The windshield wipers will stop in mid-stroke and stay there for an extended period before resuming.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat anchor tracks can cause the seat to slide back and forth or collapse, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The seat feels loose or unstable
the seat slides back and forth
the seat collapses or reclines unexpectedly
the seat bolts break or snap
the seat back frame cracks or bends.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair of the front seat anchor tracks during the recall process can lead to repeated failures, causing safety risks and inconvenience to the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The seat bolts break or snap repeatedly
the seat back frame cracks or bends
the seat feels loose or unstable
the dealer denies responsibility for further repairs.
